But there is a lot about bats that are still unknown, so the work we do here and on other properties helps us understand more about what they need to thrive.
He emphasizes the importance of searching for bats before performing maintenance in real estate, since it is possible that accidental destruction of a single nest could kill up to 400 females and young, and possibly wipe out an entire population.
Bats are peaceful and it is illegal to kill, trouble or disturb them or destroy their nests.
Elisabeth Ferrell, Scottish officer of the Bat Conservation Trust, has encouraged the public to help.
